accessibility.text: How do we solve problems recursively?
Recursion can be seen in many fields (including the arts).
In computer science recursion is often used when an iterative (loop-based) solution to a problem is too complex.
When decided to use recursion ask yourself
Can this problem be solved by breaking it down into smaller versions of itself?
Can I identify the simplest version of this problem?
Is this too hard to figure out with loops?
How do we solve problems recursively?
